  "text": "Reliability and credibility were established by using multiple data sources and team member checking, consultation with participants that used multiple 'angles of scrutiny' [CITATION_1] . The study design enabled us to cross-check interpretations with participants, which was important for analysis of digital stories. While there was a small sample size, the different data modalities (one-to one interviews, group discussion during digital story workshops, observations by three team members, digital stories) provides a depth of data for cross-reference results and ensuring the credibility of interpretations.",
